[2026-04-21T09:38:55] query='Add incremental auto-reindex â€” when any .py, .js, .ts, .jsx, .tsx file \nchanges in the repo, automatically rebuild the graph.\n\nCreate context_engine/watcher.py:\n\n1. Use watchdog library (pip install watchdog if needed)\n2. Watch the current directory for file changes \n   (.py, .js, .ts, .jsx, .tsx only)\n3. On any create/modify/delete event:\n   - Debounce 2 seconds (ignore rapid successive saves)\n   - Re-run the full index\n   - Print: "Graph updated: X nodes, Y edges (Zms)"\n4. Ignore: .cecl/, node_modules/, venv/, __pycache__/\n\nAdd a new CLI command:\n   context-engine watch .\n\nSo the workflow becomes:\n   # Terminal 1\n   context-engine watch .   # auto-updates graph on every save\n   \n   # Terminal 2  \n   claude                   # hook always has fresh context\n\nTest it:\n1. Start the watcher\n2. Touch any .py file to trigger a change\n3. Confirm graph rebuilds automatically\n4. Show me the output\n\nUpdate the README incremental updates row from \n"manual re-index" to "auto on file save via `context-engine watch`"' nodes=5 tokens=485 preview='[cli.py]\ndef _collect_js_files(root: Path) -> list[Path]\n    files: list[Path] = []\n    for ext in J'
